pg| ***** 16 ***** |


at|

When holding K5 or Q93, the extra trumps are necessary to guard your honor, therefore with these holding  the singleton lead is undesirable. |
pg| ***** 17 ***** |


at|

Similarly holding QJ4 of trumps you do not desire to ruff because you have a natural trump trick.|
pg| ***** 18 ***** |


at|

^c(3) Partner has bid. |
pg| ***** 19 ***** |


at|

The lead of a singleton cannot produce results unless you are able to give your partner the lead so that you can obtain the ruff. |
pg| ***** 20 ***** |


at|

If partner has not bid you have no reason to know that you can put him into the lead, but where he has bid the chances are very good that you can do so.|
